en_856681_0	Combat riders of 1 Special Force Regiment, together with two Russian Officers this morning (10) joined one more segment of the ongoing ‘Exercise Cormorant Strike X - 2019’ at Pulmodai town for a mock snatch operation where they stormed a bomb manufacturing hideout and captured a cache of bombs, arms and ammunition, belonging to terrorists.
en_856681_1	Showing urban fighting skills and combat riding competence they possess, those combined troops slowly but steadily and secretly circled the terrorist hideout operating on the first floor of a two-storied hardware shop building in the heart of Pulmodai town.
en_856681_2	The mock operation saw all terrorists and explosives were apprehended in the end with no damage to properties or any civilian casualties.
en_856681_3	Meanwhile, one more phase of the mock Exercise got off the ground in Trincomalee on Monday (9) morning where the troops rehearsed the recapture of oil tanks, held by terrorists in the Indian Oil Corporation (IOC) complex to be in line with the arrangements in the Exercise agenda.
en_856681_4	Troops in the 2 Commando Regiment executed the operation in Trincomalee with heli-raffling support and seaborne skills.
en_856681_5	The Special Boat Squadron (SBS) of the Sri Lanka Navy and Sri Lanka Air Force with one MI-17 helicopter actively took part in the mock Exercise.
en_856681_6	After confrontations with terrorists, troops consolidated their positions and gained control of the oil complex without causing any damage to properties or human beings.
en_856681_7	The mock Exercise on Sunday (8) moved into the hill country with full force since intelligence confirmed that the Victoria Dam in Polgolla area, runs the risk of being blasted by terrorists after placing explosive chargers along the dam.
en_856681_8	Terrorists also demanded ransom be paid to them if they were to keep off from the intended destruction.
en_856681_9	3 Commando Regiment troops making history conducted this rescue operation for the first time in order to learn more about future security challenges.
en_856681_10	Those Commandos used their Sniper skills, Heli Rappelling competence and Combat Diving skills during this mission at Polgolla.
en_856681_11	Another significant milestone of this Exercise was its use of WMZ (Mechanized Infantry Vehicles) for this daring mission for the first time in Sri Lanka as they rolled along the Victoria dam.
en_856681_12	For this mission, Sri Lanka Navy assisted providing lifesaving support and other assistance in order to resist terrorist interference that would spring from the reservoir line.
en_856681_13	One Bell 212 Helicopter of the Air Force supported the operation in heli rappelling.
en_856681_14	Exercise Director, Major General Laksiri Waduge who is also the Commander, Security Forces - Central, together with Deputy Exercise Director, Brigadier K.A Samarasiri, Exercise Brigade Commander, Commando Brigade, Lieutenant Colonel T.C.M.G.S.T Cooray and Officers took part in the mock exercise.
